7.34	Medieval_technology	Medieval technology	Medieval technology refers to the technology used in medieval Europe under Christian rule. After the Renaissance of the 12th century, medieval Europe saw a radical change in the rate of new inventions, innovations in the ways of managing traditional means of production, and economic growth. The period saw major technological advances, including the adoption of gunpowder, the invention of vertical windmills, spectacles, mechanical clocks, and greatly improved water mills, building techniques , agriculture in general (three-field crop rotation).	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/96/HGM_Pumhart_von_Steyr.jpg/220px-HGM_Pumhart_von_Steyr.jpg
